  "texts": [
    "Then we normalize x * rank to [0, 1] (Lines 4-6).Next, We traverse an implicitly constructed binary tree of depth ⌈ m 2 ⌉, where each node deterministically binds with a bit pair, from the root down to a leaf.",
    "At each level j, we use x * rank to locate the underlying node and append its bit pair to the list S (Lines 7-9, see Figure 7 for an illustration).",
    "Lines 8-9 define both the node-bit binding policy and the coupling rule between each of the 2 ⌈ m 2 ⌉ equal-sized bins and the corresponding leaf nodes.",
    "Therefore, the above procedure is equivalent to traversing the path from the root to the leaf corresponding to the bin containing x * rank, as described in Section 2.3.",
    "Finally, we truncate S to its first m entries to obtain the pseudorandom bit sequence for the target row."
  ],
